After a couple of iterations, they get arameter values very close to the "real" ones (estimated from the EGP data )

---------
MEASURING THE MEAN STRENGTH OF SELECTION:

the selection acting upon segregating polymorphisms (by randomly sampled non-synonymous polymorphism) can be estimated more accurately since this is the part of the distribution for which we have direct information.


----------
ASSUMPTIONS:

- All selected mutations are deleterious, but selection can be so weak that they are effectively neutral
-method requires that there are two types of sites : a set of sites at which all mutations are neutral and sites at which some of themutations are subject to selection. We assume here that mutations in introns are neutral and estimate the distribution of fitness effects for mutations that change an amino acid.
-Free recombinations between sites
