-They assume the deviations of the intron distribution from a truly neutral one is due to expansion and/or admixture

------------------------
RESULTS:

Estimated DFE from the site freq spectrum of both non-synonymous and intron sites is:
shape parameter = 0.23 with 95{\%} credibility intervals of 0.19–0.27 and the mean of (strength of selection) the distribution to be 425 (225, 766)
-the vast majority of amino-acid-changing mutations in humans have mild effects of between 1/1000 and 1/10.

------------------------
LIMITATIONS:

There are limitations for estimating the DFE for strongly selected mutations, as to be able to see them segragating in a population you would need a huge sample size.},
