In protein coding sequences, the proportion of adaptive non-synonimous susbstitutions has been estimated to be about 50{\%} between Drosophila species (ref 61-63, but 64). Also, it is estimated for Drosophila that around 15{\%} of non-coding substitutions are adaptive driven (ref49)

DELETERIOUS MUTATIONS
