Then they demonstrate that for this mechanism of pattern formation the cell motility is necessary, so the mechanism is inherently "morphodynamic"(sensu isaac).


However, it seems to me that they dont explore the possibility of pattern formation in a morphostatic way exhaustively, and one assumption in the morphostatic model is that the diffusion for both galectins is the same. I wonder if having different diffusion the morphostatic system can produce some pattern.


In general, the system is a variant of the local activation and lateral inhibition (LALI) model and doesnt need to be considered as another dynamic patterning module of newmans cathegory.},
